Inverness defender Josh Meekings was banned for a handball in the Scottish Cup semi-final against Celtic . 
  The SFA changed the rules to retrospectively ban players after a challenge by Gary Deegan on Gary Irvine in 2013 . 
  The PFA Scotland chief executive Fraser Wishart believes the rules have gone too far . 
  Inverness won the game 2-1 at Celtic Park . 
 